{
  "texts": [
    "Ethereum's programmable and decentralized nature allows developers to create complex smart contracts and decentralized applications (dapp).",
    "However, this also opens up attack vectors that malicious actors can exploit in several scenarios.",
    "Attackers exploit smart contract vulnerabilities in four key ways.",
    "First, they insert code bugs to steal funds or brick contracts (Aziz et al., 2022; Aljofey et al., 2022; Kim et al., 2019; Wang et al., 2020; Liu et al., 2022; Md et al., 2023; Pahuja and Kamal).",
    "Second, they manipulate cryptography to alter outcomes (Zhang et al., 2022)."
  ]
}